==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pinic
<hw>Pi"nic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pinus</ets>
pine.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the pine;
obtained from the pine; formerly, designating an acid which is the chief
constituent of common resin, -- now called <xex>abietic</xex>, or
<xex>sylvic</xex>, <xex>acid</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pining</ent>⟦br⟧
